&lt;p&gt;CONSULTANT IN TRAUMA &amp; ORTHOPAEDICS - SUB SPECIALISING IN HAND SURGERY&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We require an enthusiastic and dynamic Orthopaedic Hand Consultant to join our Trauma and Orthopaedic Department in a substantive post. The successful applicant will assist in the delivery of both trauma and elective hand surgery, and will take part in the general Orthopaedic trauma on call rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fracture and elective clinics are held in Tunbridge Wells, Maidstone and peripheral hospitals. Day surgery lists and inpatient elective lists occur in Tunbridge Wells and Maidstone and trauma lists at Tunbridge Wells. The department provides a Consultant delivered trauma service seven days a week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust provides general hospital services to a population of approximately 480,000 in West Kent and North East Sussex, and some specialist services to a considerably larger population. Around 120,000 new patients present each year to the A&amp;E departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunities to develop personal interests such as management, research, governance, and medical education within the new Kent medical school are encouraged.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Trust is situated in a beautiful part of South East England with great transport links and some of the finest state and private schools in the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must possess or be within 6 months of CCT on the interview date.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date : 11th December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
